text: Oenomaus may refer to: * Oenomaus, a king of Pisa in Greek mythology * Oenomaus (butterfly), a gossamer-winged butterfly genus * Oenomaus (rebel slave) (c. 72 BC), Gallic rebel gladiator who fought in the Third Servile War * Oenomaus of Gadara (2nd century AD), Cynic philosopher
title: Oenomaus (disambiguation)
